1
00:00:00,876 --> 00:00:02,920
(MOUSE SQUEAKS)

2
00:00:02,961 --> 00:00:03,670
(PENGUINS CHIRP)

3
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:06,632
(ALL CHEERING)

4
00:00:09,426 --> 00:00:10,511
(SCREECHES)

5
00:00:10,552 --> 00:00:11,553
(QUACKS)

6
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:13,764
Adventure Time

7
00:00:13,805 --> 00:00:15,140
Come on, grab your friends

8
00:00:15,182 --> 00:00:17,893
We'll go to very distant lands

9
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:20,020
With Jake the dog
and Finn the human

10
00:00:20,103 --> 00:00:21,522
The fun will never end

11
00:00:21,647 --> 00:00:23,982
It's Adventure Time

12
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:35,827
BOTH: Calling all Curlys!

13
00:00:35,911 --> 00:00:37,704
(BEEPING)

14
00:00:39,581 --> 00:00:40,958
- Curly! Curly!
- Curly! Curly!

15
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:42,584
- Curly! Curly!
- Curly!

16
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:44,086
Called!

17
00:00:44,211 --> 00:00:45,462
- Yeah!
- All right!

18
00:00:45,546 --> 00:00:47,339
One more, and we'll have called all the Curlys!

19
00:00:47,464 --> 00:00:48,674
I know!

20
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:50,551
- Curly! Curly!
- Curly! Curly!

21
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:51,843
ANNOUNCER: We interrupt this video game

22
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:53,303
for a special news flash!

23
00:00:53,345 --> 00:00:54,346
- No!
- No!

24
00:00:54,471 --> 00:00:56,306
Ahh! Save game, save game!

25
00:00:56,348 --> 00:00:58,350
It's okay, Beemo.
What's the emergency?

26
00:00:58,475 --> 00:00:59,560
Hold, please.

27
00:00:59,601 --> 00:01:03,063
ANNOUNCER: This just in.
President Porpoise is missing!

28
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:04,314
(GASPS)

29
00:01:04,439 --> 00:01:06,191
Who's President Porpoise?
Is he real?

30
00:01:06,191 --> 00:01:07,693
He's real, and he's missing!

31
00:01:08,151 --> 00:01:09,194
Mmm...

32
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:11,321
He is real! We video chat sometimes.

33
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:14,157
We need to find him before
they give the oath of office

34
00:01:14,199 --> 00:01:15,909
to Vice President Blowfish.

35
00:01:15,951 --> 00:01:17,077
BEEMO: That creep!

36
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:20,289
Okay, let's go find President Porpoise.

37
00:01:20,330 --> 00:01:22,791
I guess we should ask Banana Man
if we can borrow his submarine.

38
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:24,918
- BANANA MAN: No problemo!
- (BOTH SCREAM)

39
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:27,421
Anything to help the friend of my friend.

40
00:01:27,462 --> 00:01:30,465
Uh... What are ya doing
behind our couch, neighbor?

41
00:01:30,549 --> 00:01:31,842
Sometimes I get Ionely

42
00:01:31,925 --> 00:01:34,303
and need to hear the sound
of other people talking.

43
00:01:34,970 --> 00:01:37,347
We should let it slide so we can use his sub.

44
00:01:37,556 --> 00:01:39,808
But only if I can go with you guys.

45
00:01:39,850 --> 00:01:42,728
Nobody steers the S.S. Inquisitive but me!

46
00:01:42,811 --> 00:01:44,354
Then it's the three of us!

47
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:45,564
Four!

48
00:01:45,606 --> 00:01:46,690
(ALL LAUGH)

49
00:01:46,732 --> 00:01:48,609
- ICE KING: Five!
- (ALL SCREAM)

50
00:01:49,484 --> 00:01:50,986
(CHUCKLES)

51
00:01:51,069 --> 00:01:52,613
Uh... Anybody else?

52
00:01:54,573 --> 00:01:56,074
Okay, let's go!

53
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:16,803
As soon as I finish loading
these supplies, we can ship out.

54
00:02:17,262 --> 00:02:20,015
Finn, you're my first mate.

55
00:02:20,057 --> 00:02:21,391
Nice.

56
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:23,935
Jake, you're my morale officer.

57
00:02:24,061 --> 00:02:27,689
You keep our spirits up
while the sub is down.

58
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:30,442
Dude, we're both big-shot officers!

59
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:31,818
What's my job, Finn?

60
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:34,446
You have the most important
job of all, Beemo...

61
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:36,406
To distract Ice King until we get away.

62
00:02:41,328 --> 00:02:44,331
That decision was good for morale!

63
00:02:44,414 --> 00:02:45,457
(BOTH LAUGH)

64
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:46,458
(SUBMARINE POWERS ON)

65
00:02:50,087 --> 00:02:51,171
Aah!

66
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:55,801
Hey! You forgot me and the cabin boy here!

67
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:56,927
Hey!

68
00:02:56,968 --> 00:02:59,554
Shh! We are on the submarine.

69
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:01,682
What? No, we're not!

70
00:03:01,723 --> 00:03:02,933
Yes, see?

71
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:06,353
(MIMICS BEEPING NOISES AND WHIRRING)

72
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:08,689
Beep, beep, beep...

73
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:10,982
Think we'll see any beautiful mermaids?

74
00:03:11,066 --> 00:03:14,069
Get serious, Lieutenant!
We're in dangerous waters!

75
00:03:14,111 --> 00:03:15,487
Aye-aye, sirl

76
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:20,867
I'm locking in the coordinates

77
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:23,745
for the last-known whereabouts
of President Porpoise.

78
00:03:24,246 --> 00:03:25,330
Aye-aye, sirl

79
00:03:25,372 --> 00:03:27,624
Hey, Jake, do you think I'm doing a good job,

80
00:03:27,749 --> 00:03:29,000
like, as a first mate or whatever?

81
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,877
Yeah, man, you're doing great...

82
00:03:31,002 --> 00:03:32,713
Considering we're all gonna die.

83
00:03:32,754 --> 00:03:34,339
- Wait, what?
- We're all gonna die.

84
00:03:34,381 --> 00:03:36,883
You're supposed to be keepin'
our spirits up, remember?

85
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:39,010
Yeah, but it's so cramped in here.

86
00:03:39,136 --> 00:03:40,387
Ooh! BRB!

87
00:03:41,012 --> 00:03:43,765
- Jake?
- Yeah, man, I'm fine.

88
00:03:43,849 --> 00:03:46,017
- I just had to shrink down a little!
- What?

89
00:03:46,101 --> 00:03:47,894
Look at all this room I have!

90
00:03:47,978 --> 00:03:50,772
Ha, cha-cha-cha... Whoa! (SCREAMS)

91
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:53,525
- Jake!
- (SCREAMS)

92
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:54,651
I'm good!

93
00:03:54,735 --> 00:03:56,027
- What?
- BANANA MAN: Hey, Finn?

94
00:03:56,111 --> 00:03:58,864
Can you come help me
calibrate the windshield wiper fluid valve?

95
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:01,533
Whoa, whoa! Whoa!

96
00:04:01,867 --> 00:04:03,535
Ahhh!

97
00:04:03,618 --> 00:04:04,619
I'm good!

98
00:04:04,661 --> 00:04:06,288
(LAUGHS) What?

99
00:04:06,788 --> 00:04:08,290
Look at how small I am.

100
00:04:08,415 --> 00:04:09,499
(LAUGHS)

101
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:11,251
When did you get so claustrophobic?

102
00:04:11,293 --> 00:04:13,795
It's a middle-age thing, I think.

103
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:17,758
Okay, I guess I can calibrate it by myself.

104
00:04:20,844 --> 00:04:23,013
(CHUCKLES) Me too, huh, guys?

105
00:04:23,096 --> 00:04:24,347
(CHUCKLES) You see that?

106
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:26,725
(CLAMORING)

107
00:04:27,476 --> 00:04:30,020
Will my colleague from
the Great Kelp Forest yield?

108
00:04:30,145 --> 00:04:31,396
Thank you.

109
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:34,024
The President is missing.
Yes, we all agree.

110
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:35,108
And while he is missing,

111
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:37,486
Vice President Blowfish is acting president.

112
00:04:37,527 --> 00:04:39,529
Again, yes, agree.

113
00:04:39,613 --> 00:04:41,615
But to swear in a new president

114
00:04:41,656 --> 00:04:43,992
while the current one is missing?

115
00:04:44,034 --> 00:04:45,410
Do not agree!

116
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:49,039
This is an outrage, Secretary Octopus!

117
00:04:49,122 --> 00:04:53,043
Undersea law dictates that
when the clock strikes 5:00,

118
00:04:53,168 --> 00:04:56,004
I become President!

119
00:04:56,046 --> 00:04:59,049
You're not allowed to puff out
in the court of food!

120
00:04:59,132 --> 00:05:00,050
(CRASH)

121
00:05:02,511 --> 00:05:05,138
Attention, Fish Parliament!
We're here to help!

122
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:08,433
Who and what are you?

123
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:10,393
Jake, get up here!

124
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:12,145
Stuck again!

125
00:05:12,187 --> 00:05:14,689
My brother video chats sometimes
with the President.

126
00:05:14,815 --> 00:05:17,067
I'm a good friend of President Porpoise!

127
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:18,568
(ALL MURMURING)

128
00:05:19,528 --> 00:05:20,821
(SIGHS)

129
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:31,206
Hi. Oh!

130
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:32,666
(SIGHS) Aw.

131
00:05:32,707 --> 00:05:35,460
Boy, when I first signed up for this adventure,

132
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:37,587
I just wanted to see pretty mermaids.

133
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:40,465
But now I realize it's all about the camaraderie

134
00:05:40,549 --> 00:05:42,467
of my fellow sailors, you know?

135
00:05:42,551 --> 00:05:44,594
I do know. I had a feeling you'd...

136
00:05:44,678 --> 00:05:47,097
Hmm. I don't like the look of this.

137
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,473
Everything okay, sir?

138
00:05:48,557 --> 00:05:50,058
No. We are running out of air.

139
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:52,727
- (GASPS)
- We need to surface immediately.

140
00:05:52,853 --> 00:05:54,479
But if we show ourselves now,

141
00:05:54,563 --> 00:05:56,857
the enemy will be right on top of us!

142
00:05:56,940 --> 00:05:58,191
Shh!

143
00:05:58,233 --> 00:05:59,484
(MURMURING)

144
00:05:59,568 --> 00:06:01,361
FINN: Please, just give us a chance!

145
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:03,613
(GRUNTS) Just make me president!

146
00:06:04,239 --> 00:06:06,366
Don't trust these filthy surface boys!

147
00:06:06,992 --> 00:06:09,870
I guess it is kind of weird
that you guys just showed up

148
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:11,580
and you're not even fish.

149
00:06:11,621 --> 00:06:14,207
We're mammals, just like President Porpoise!

150
00:06:14,249 --> 00:06:16,376
Yeah, man! Nerves and fur.

151
00:06:16,501 --> 00:06:18,211
Oh, that's a good point!

152
00:06:18,253 --> 00:06:19,379
Uh, wait!

153
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:21,840
I demand this be put to a vote!

154
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:23,341
Wow, this is intense!

155
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:25,886
Okay, everyone who thinks
these guys should just go away,

156
00:06:25,969 --> 00:06:28,471
raise your fins or claws or whatever.

157
00:06:28,513 --> 00:06:30,098
Two, four, five...

158
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:33,226
And with Governor Anglerfish, that's seven.

159
00:06:35,145 --> 00:06:37,355
Oh, eight? Wow. All right, eight.

160
00:06:37,606 --> 00:06:39,399
And everyone who wants them to stay

161
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:40,984
and help find the President?

162
00:06:41,026 --> 00:06:42,027
No one?

163
00:06:42,611 --> 00:06:45,280
Oh, wait. Representative Sybil.

164
00:06:45,363 --> 00:06:46,656
(GASPS)

165
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:49,743
Well, if that's everyone,
then the final vote is...

166
00:06:49,784 --> 00:06:52,537
Wait! I haven't voted yet.

167
00:06:52,621 --> 00:06:53,663
Ahh...

168
00:06:53,747 --> 00:06:56,499
Ah! There! Now it's nine to eight!

169
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:58,251
SECRETARY OCTOPUS: The yeas have it.

170
00:06:58,293 --> 00:06:59,920
Finn and Jake, you have

171
00:07:00,045 --> 00:07:02,297
20 minutes to find the President!

172
00:07:03,423 --> 00:07:05,800
They must give a 20-minute presentation first!

173
00:07:06,927 --> 00:07:09,137
We're on to you, Blowfish!

174
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:11,640
(PANTING)

175
00:07:12,641 --> 00:07:13,767
Stay collected, Lieutenant!

176
00:07:13,808 --> 00:07:17,562
We'll get you home to the
children you speak of so fondly!

177
00:07:17,646 --> 00:07:20,148
It's no good. My guns are barkin'.

178
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,524
(GASPS)

179
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:22,567
(GRUNTS)

180
00:07:23,151 --> 00:07:25,445
Pull yourself together, Lieutenant!

181
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:28,198
Slap, slap! I bring my boys home!

182
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:30,951
(GRUNTING)

183
00:07:32,077 --> 00:07:33,662
Careful, I bruise easily.

184
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:36,831
FINN: You're acting highly sus,
VP Blowfish!

185
00:07:36,915 --> 00:07:38,792
I suspect you may have had a hand

186
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,336
- in Prez Porp's disappearance!
- (ALL GASP)

187
00:07:41,336 --> 00:07:43,588
VP BLOWFISH: You be quiet!
You're not right!

188
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:45,966
Okay, guys! I'm going to go look for clues!

189
00:07:46,424 --> 00:07:50,679
Something about this
whole situation smells fishy!

190
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,305
Ah! Ha-ha!

191
00:07:52,347 --> 00:07:53,473
Whoa!

192
00:07:53,598 --> 00:07:55,225
(MURMURING)

193
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:56,935
I'm headed out!

194
00:07:56,977 --> 00:07:59,104
Wouldn't say no to company!

195
00:08:00,355 --> 00:08:01,856
President Porpoise!

196
00:08:01,982 --> 00:08:04,067
President Porpoise?

197
00:08:04,109 --> 00:08:06,236
President...

198
00:08:07,946 --> 00:08:09,698
It's like there's this instruction manual

199
00:08:09,739 --> 00:08:11,825
that explains how to talk to people

200
00:08:11,866 --> 00:08:15,370
and everyone in the world
got a copy except me.

201
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:18,248
Ow! (CHUCKLES) Just, uh, taking a break.

202
00:08:18,331 --> 00:08:19,749
Gonna keep looking!

203
00:08:20,375 --> 00:08:22,377
Uh, what?

204
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:24,713
(GIGGLES)

205
00:08:24,754 --> 00:08:26,381
(SCREAMS)

206
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:33,930
(SINGING) We've only just met

207
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:37,684
We've barely said a word to each other yet

208
00:08:37,809 --> 00:08:40,687
But already I know that

209
00:08:42,397 --> 00:08:44,190
We fit

210
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:49,571
Yes, two halves make a whole

211
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:52,532
And wholes are whole

212
00:08:53,324 --> 00:08:55,952
Like an arm through a sleeve

213
00:08:56,077 --> 00:08:57,078
(GROANING)

214
00:08:57,162 --> 00:09:00,415
Or a cup into a movie seat

215
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:04,210
You haven't said a word to me

216
00:09:04,294 --> 00:09:05,462
(GIGGLES)

217
00:09:06,171 --> 00:09:10,050
Only just giggled gleefully

218
00:09:10,592 --> 00:09:11,843
Uh, security!

219
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:13,553
But already I know that

220
00:09:16,181 --> 00:09:17,849
We fit

221
00:09:19,059 --> 00:09:21,478
Yeah, we fit

222
00:09:22,479 --> 00:09:25,482
You're kissing my space helmet

223
00:09:25,607 --> 00:09:28,443
And already I know

224
00:09:30,445 --> 00:09:33,364
That two halves make a whole

225
00:09:36,201 --> 00:09:37,452
This has been so nice.

226
00:09:37,494 --> 00:09:41,372
But I should probably go help my
friends find President Porpoise.

227
00:09:41,498 --> 00:09:43,208
Eh, come on, who cares?

228
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:44,375
Oh!

229
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:47,754
But he's your president.

230
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:50,507
National politics don't really
represent my interests.

231
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:52,383
(CHUCKLES) Okay.

232
00:09:52,884 --> 00:09:54,886
Talk, Blowfish! Where's the President?

233
00:09:54,969 --> 00:09:58,389
I don't know where he is!
I'm the President now!

234
00:09:58,890 --> 00:10:00,266
- (CLOCK CHIMES)
- (LAUGHS EVILLY)

235
00:10:00,350 --> 00:10:01,476
Oh, no, bro!

236
00:10:01,518 --> 00:10:03,269
- (SCREAMS)
- Do not agree!

237
00:10:04,729 --> 00:10:06,648
- (CHIRPS)
- Huh?

238
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,528
President Porpoise! But where have you...

239
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:13,154
- (CLICKS)
- A three-day weekend?

240
00:10:13,238 --> 00:10:15,240
I don't remember you mentioning that.

241
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:18,535
I tied a string to my tentacle
to remind myself?

242
00:10:18,785 --> 00:10:23,873
Nope, nope, nope, nope, nope, nope, NOpe...

243
00:10:23,915 --> 00:10:26,126
No... Oh! Well, T'll be!

244
00:10:26,167 --> 00:10:28,670
Isn't it always on the last arm
you check? (CHUCKLES)

245
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:31,798
Please, Finn and Jake,
when you return to dry land,

246
00:10:31,881 --> 00:10:34,134
tell no one of our lax record-keeping.

247
00:10:34,509 --> 00:10:36,636
Ah, don't worry, Secretary Octopus.

248
00:10:36,678 --> 00:10:39,681
We wouldn't want to deflate anyone's ego!

249
00:10:39,764 --> 00:10:42,433
(BOTH LAUGH)

250
00:10:44,936 --> 00:10:47,397
Huh? Ahh! Oh! (CLEARS THROAT)

251
00:10:48,022 --> 00:10:50,900
My kids must be worried sick!

252
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:53,319
(HIGH-PITCHED SQUEAKING)

253
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:55,572
Man, I can't understand a word you're saying.

254
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:57,323
I said, where's Banana Man?

255
00:10:57,407 --> 00:11:00,076
We're getting low on air, and I'm freaking out.

256
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,829
Uh, maybe there's a radio or something.

257
00:11:02,954 --> 00:11:04,664
- Huh?
- Oh! Oh!

258
00:11:04,706 --> 00:11:05,957
Aargh!

259
00:11:06,082 --> 00:11:07,333
(LAUGHTER)

260
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:09,085
You know what, bro? I'm glad you're here.

261
00:11:09,169 --> 00:11:12,839
JAKE: 'Cause dying together sucks
a little less than dying alone.

262
00:11:14,966 --> 00:11:18,344
Come along with me

263
00:11:19,095 --> 00:11:22,807
